// An `if`/`else` body may be a bare statement (no `{ }`): a single `yield`
// (or `return`/`exit`, or a bare expression) is allowed directly, like `for`.
// Each branch here yields directly; nested `else if` chains work too.
fn String classify() String {
    if (false) yield "first" else if (true) yield "second" else yield "third"
}

classify
